Latest notes that you can refer for GIT: https://github.com/JanbaskDevops/studyMatarial/tree/main/JanBask

Lets install jenkins
=====================
[Link] https://www.jenkins.io/download/ 

Jenkins have 2 types release-

1) LTS Release Line
Long-Term Support (LTS) release baselines are chosen every 12 weeks from the stream of regular releases. Every 4 weeks we release stable releases which include bug and security fix backports.

2) Regular releases (Weekly)
This release line delivers bug fixes and new features rapidly to users and plugin developers who need them. It is generally delivered on a weekly cadence.

This release line delivers bug fixes and new features rapidly to users and plugin developers who need them. It is generally delivered on a weekly cadence.

[Change log] https://www.jenkins.io/changelog/
It shows the summary of product changes history.

Mostly whatever tools we have learn in devops, they are supporting --version/ version command.

When you are running --version/version command, you will get below output
<MajorRelease><MinorRelease><FixPack>

ubuntu $ git --version
git version 2.25.1

ubuntu $ docker --version
Docker version 24.0.5

Jenkins installation steps

1) Jenkins in written in Java, so we need to install java first

2) https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian-stable/

Initial password: Jenkins will give you initial passowrd that you can use during setup. it like bank is giving you internet id and password in day1.


Setup in docker
docker run -idt -p 8080:8080 georgespasov/docker-jenkins
docker exect -it <container name> /bin/bash
cat ./var/jenkins_home/secrets/initialAdminPassword


Docker compose
==============
Docker compose is a tool and it's by default installed in docker playground

git clone https://github.com/JanbaskDevops/dockerCompose.git
cd dockerCompose
docker compose up


Putty: Putty is a third party tool that allow us to to login to anyserver with the help of id and password

in linux multiple user are there, but two popular users are-
1) ubuntu > least privilage
2) root > most privillage

ubuntu@ip-172-31-13-210:~$ apt install docker.io
E: Could not open lock file /var/lib/dpkg/lock-frontend - open (13: Permission denied)
E: Unable to acquire the dpkg frontend lock (/var/lib/dpkg/lock-frontend), are you root?






















How to use putty?
sudo su -




